---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — 1Quest Learn"
  description="Why we built 1Quest Learn and how it fits into the broader 1Quest product."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="page-title">About <span class="grad">1Quest</span></h1>
    <p class="lede">
      We build tools for learners who care about understanding — not just finishing a syllabus checkbox.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>What this site is</h2>
    <p>
      This marketing site is the public face of <strong>1Quest Learn</strong>: articles, topic hubs,
      and guides that help you discover what to study and why it matters. The interactive tutor,
      account features, and full product live in the main 1Quest app.
    </p>

    <h2>What we believe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Good explanations beat long lists of facts.</li>
      <li>Structure reduces anxiety when the syllabus is huge.</li>
      <li>Technology should adapt to how you actually study — not the other way around.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What's next</h2>
    <p>
      We'll add lesson pages, blog posts, and syllabus-aligned hubs here over time. For now, this
      is a clean foundation: fast pages, clear navigation, and room to grow.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
